      <scopecontent id="aspace_a9521f10136a27e86ea0507973903ce5">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Stutz Collection consists of correspondence of Nazi Party officials, including Hitler, Goering, and Goebbels (1928-1944). Several letters are to Nazi officials from other sources including one from Cardinal Pacelli, later Pope Pius XII. Letters to Franz Gurtner and Otto George Thierack from Himmler and Heydrich reveal the political intrigue and extra-legal practices carried on without the knowledge of the Ministry of Justice. Also included in the collection are postcards showing Hitler and other Third Reich officials.</p>
         <p>Since the collection is entirely in German, the more important items have been translated into English and interfiled with the individual letters in the collection.</p>
         <p>For more information about the collection, please consult the following<ref actuate="onrequest"
                 href="http://mssa.altfindingaids.library.yale.edu/mssa.ms.0204/mssa_ms_0204_documenting_the_third_reich.pdf"
                 linktitle="article"
                 show="new">article</ref>:</p>
         <p>Gotlieb, Howard B. "Documenting the Third Reich: The Stutz Collection of Nazi Manuscripts." <emph render="italic">Yale University Library Gazette</emph> 37.3(1963): 109-117.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
